devdoc.details: An ownable contract that can be used as a storage where the variables are stored in a set of mappings indexed by hash name Contract importing following the guidelines in the zeppelinos upgreadability contracts post:  https://github.com/zeppelinos/labs/tree/ff479995ed90c4dbb5e32294fa95b16a22bb99c8/upgradeability_using_eternal_storage

constructor.details: The constructor sets the original `owner` of the contract to the sender account.

getAddress(bytes32).details: Get the value stored of a address variable by the hash name

params.h: The keccak256 hash of the variable name

getBoolean(bytes32).details: Get the value stored of a boolean variable by the hash name

params.h: The keccak256 hash of the variable name

getBytes(bytes32).details: Get the value stored of a bytes variable by the hash name

params.h: The keccak256 hash of the variable name

getInt(bytes32).details: Get the value stored of a int variable by the hash name

params.h: The keccak256 hash of the variable name

getString(bytes32).details: Get the value stored of a string variable by the hash name

params.h: The keccak256 hash of the variable name

getUint(bytes32).details: Get the value stored of a uint variable by the hash name

params.h: The keccak256 hash of the variable name

isOwner().return: true if `msg.sender` is the owner of the contract.

renounceOwnership().details: Allows the current owner to relinquish control of the contract.

setAddress(bytes32,address).details: Allows the owner to set a value for a address variable.

params.h: The keccak256 hash of the variable name

setBoolean(bytes32,bool).details: Allows the owner to set a value for a boolean variable.

params.h: The keccak256 hash of the variable name

setBytes(bytes32,bytes).details: Allows the owner to set a value for a bytes variable.

params.h: The keccak256 hash of the variable name

setInt(bytes32,int256).details: Allows the owner to set a value for a int variable.

params.h: The keccak256 hash of the variable name

setString(bytes32,string).details: Allows the owner to set a value for a string variable.

params.h: The keccak256 hash of the variable name

setUint(bytes32,uint256).details: Allows the owner to set a value for a boolean variable.

params.h: The keccak256 hash of the variable name

transferOwnership(address).details: Allows the current owner to transfer control of the contract to a newOwner.

params.newOwner: The address to transfer ownership to.

devdoc.title: EternalStorage

renounceOwnership().notice: Renouncing to ownership will leave the contract without an owner. It will not be possible to call the functions with the `onlyOwner` modifier anymore.
